<h1>Features of the Antimony language </h1>  </div>
</div>
<div class="contents">
<p>Antimony is designed to be:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Human-readable</b>. It should be possible to look at an Antimony model and understand what's going on.</li>
<li><b>Human-writable</b>. It should be possible to conceive of a model and create an Antimony model by hand.</li>
<li><b>Modular</b>. Different Antimony models should be able to be combined to create more complex models that are easier to understand due to their compartmentalized nature.</li>
<li><b>Accessible to genetic networks</b>. A special syntax was developed specifically for the design of genetic networks, in keeping with the principles above--these networks should also be understandable, modular, and easily combined.</li>
</ul>
<p>Some other model definition languages do feature one or more of the above characteristics, but Antimony is (we believe) the first to feature all four in a single language.</p>
